{
  "texts": [
    "This same conclusion was corroborated when common images were used instead of histopathologic images [17].In the realm of histopathology images, minority class oversampling has gained prominence, particularly in binary classification problems [19][20][21][22][23].",
    "However, applying oversampling in object detection scenarios presents unique challenges, as a single image or patch may contain multiple examples, some belonging to minority classes and others to majority classes.",
    "Addressing this challenge, Hagos et al.",
    "proposed the creation of a weight matrix, where each cell carries a weighted value.",
    "This matrix is subsequently employed in the weighted dice overlap loss function to mitigate the effects of class imbalance [24]."
  ]
}